<br>
Supposedly Kunark, Velious and Luclin are no longer around for players to visit anymore ;p It's back to good old skool Norrath (Antonica, Odus and Faydwer). now. 500 yrs into the future (This is for folks who've not read about it on the new website yet), and the possibility of having our current PC's in EQ having decendants we play in the future.<br>
<br>
The new player Classification seems interesting..<br>
<br>
Works like this form what I understand:<br>
<br>
PLayers start out as everyday humbodies, you pick Race, sex and facial/hair features and begin play, no picking stats.<br>
<br>
at lvl 9 you choose a base profession, Fighter, Priest, rogue, Crusader,  etc.<br>
<br>
At 30 you &quot;graduate&quot; to a specialized class, Fighter &gt; War/monk/etc, Priest &gt; SHaman, Druid, Cleric; Crusader &gt; Paladin, SK.<br>
<br>
100 lvl limit cap (I think)<br>
<br>
and a mix of original/Reimagined zones and new zones/areas to explore.<br>
<br>
Seamless zoneing (FINALLY!)<br>
<br>
several Non-Confrentational advancement paths (merchants/tradeskills/etc). Wow, make leather all day and DING! ;p<br>
<br>
new graphics engine and higher poly count models, I'm imagine you'll need a hoss of a PC from the SS's I've seen.<br>
<br>
Seems cool. I swore long ago never to buy another veriant product, but from my experience, your gonna have problems across the board no matter where you go or play. I guess it's a choosing of the lesser evils ;p<br>
<br>
I'll definatly give it a try, just so I can play another druid to 50 /grin<br>
<br>
